{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Update your code to make use of the new state sharing tools in the library, such as the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Shared"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"property wrapper, and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appStorage"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"fileStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" persistence strategies."}],"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.15","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.14","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.13","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.12","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.11","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.9","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.8","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.7","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.6","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.5","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.4"],"generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library only introduced new"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"APIs and did not deprecate any existing APIs.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"tools of version 1.9. See ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"},{"type":"text","text":" for more information."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Important","style":"important","type":"aside"},{"anchor":"Sharing-state","level":2,"text":"Sharing state","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The new tools added are concerned with allowing one to seamlessly share state with many parts of an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"application that is easy to understand, and most importantly, testable. See the dedicated"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState"},{"type":"text","text":" article for more information on how to use these new tools."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To share state in one feature with another feature, simply use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Shared"},{"text":" property wrapper:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared var signUpData: SignUpData","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This will require that ","type":"text"},{"code":"SignUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" be passed in from the parent, and any changes made to this state","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will be instantly observed by all features holding onto it.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Further, there are persistence strategies one can employ in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Shared"},{"text":". For example, if you want any","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"changes of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signUpData"},{"type":"text","text":" to be automatically persisted to the file system you can use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)"},{"text":" and specify a URL:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["@ObservableState","struct State {","  @Shared(.fileStorage(URL(\/* ... *\/) var signUpData = SignUpData()","  \/\/ ...","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Upon app launch the ","type":"text"},{"code":"signUpData","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be populated from disk, and any changes made to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signUpData"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will automatically be persisted to disk. Further, if the disk version changes, all instances of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signUpData"},{"type":"text","text":" in the application will automatically update."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is another persistence strategy for storing simple data types in user defaults, called"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appStorage"},{"text":". It can refer to a value in user defaults by a string","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"key:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@ObservableState ","struct State {","  @Shared(.appStorage(\"isOn\")) var isOn = false","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Similar to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage(_:decoder:encoder:)"},{"text":", upon launch of the application the initial","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"value of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isOn"},{"text":" will be populated from user defaults, and any change to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isOn"},{"type":"text","text":" will be automatically"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"persisted to user defaults. Further, if the user defaults value changes, all instances of "},{"code":"isOn","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"in the application will automatically update.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"That is the basics of sharing data. Be sure to see the dedicated ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState"},{"type":"text","text":" article"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for more detailed information."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.10","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.10"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"title":"Migrating to 1.10","roleHeading":"Article"},"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/documentation/ComposableArchitecture/MigratingTo1.14":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.14","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Store","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" type is